<head>

<title>POSSIBLY-RECOVER</title>
</head>

<body>

	<h3><i>I possibly lose my infection and change my state to recovered.</i> 
	</h3>
	<p><font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	</p>
	<p><b>POSSIBLY-RECOVER</b></p>
	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>do-every <i>1</i>
   [do-with-probability 1<i> /</i> the-average-duration-of-infection
       [add-behaviours list-of-micro-behaviours "Recovery Behaviours" [SET-STATE-RECOVERED.html]
        remove-behaviours list-of-micro-behaviours "Behaviours to Remove" [POSSIBLY-RECOVER.html]]]</pre>
	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>

	<p><a href="RECOVERY-POSSIBLE-AFTER-INFECTION.html">RECOVERY-POSSIBLE-AFTER-INFECTION</a> 
	starts this process when this agent become infected.</p>
	<p><a title="POSSIBLY-LOSE-IMMUNITY" href="POSSIBLY-LOSE-IMMUNITY.html">POSSIBLY-LOSE-IMMUNITY</a> works in a similar manner. 
	This relies upon <i>the-average-duration-of-infection </i>which is defined by
	<a href="CREATE-RATE-OF-RECOVERY-SLIDER.html">CREATE-RATE-OF-RECOVERY-SLIDER</a>.
	<a href="RECOVERY-POSSIBLE-AFTER-INFECTION.html">
	RECOVERY-POSSIBLE-AFTER-INFECTION</a> ensures that this micro-behaviour can 
	be added when an agent becomes infected.</p>
	<p>You may wish to add the <a href="RECOVERY-POSSIBLE-AFTER-INFECTION.html">RECOVERY-POSSIBLE-AFTER-INFECTION</a> micro-behaviour to implement recovery.</p>
	<h2>How this works</h2>
	<p>Every <i>second</i>, with probability of <i>1</i> / 
	<i>the-average-duration-of-infection, </i>this resets my state to <i>recovered</i>. Once 
	recovered I no longer need to run this micro-behaviour anymore so it is 
	removed.</p>
	<h2>Models that use this</h2>
	<p>
	<a href="Library.html#Epidemic_model">A sample model of an epidemic spreading over a social network</a> uses this micro-behaviour.</p>
